HEADWORD: chilblains
<hw>chil"blains</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Chill</ets> + <ets>Blain</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
blain, sore, or inflammatory swelling of the feet or hands, produced by
exposure to cold, and attended by itching, pain, and sometimes
ulceration.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> pernio.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

